						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Maduraikoṇḍa Parakēsarivarman (Parāntaka I.): Year 25 = 931-32 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is incomplete.</p>						

						<p>It appears to record a gift of land by Ambalavaṉ Aiyyāṟaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Iṟaivāṉkuḍi-kiḻavan for providing music on the three occasions <hi rend="italic">(sandhi)</hi> of worship everyday to the god Tiruppulippagavar of Śiṟṟiṅgūṟ. Among the lands forming a boundary to the gift land is one gifted to the god Vināyakaṉpagavaṉ.</p>						

						</summary>
